"equals sign (=). For example, the query ``tag:\"=science\"`` will match "
"\"science\", but not \"science fiction\" or \"hard science\". Regular "
"expression searches are indicated by prefixing the search string with a "
"tilde (~). Any `Python-compatible regular expression "
"<https://docs.python.org/2/library/re.html>`_ can be used. Note that "
"backslashes used to escape special characters in regular expressions must be"
" doubled because single backslashes will be removed during query parsing. "
"For example, to match a literal parenthesis you must enter ``\\\\(``. "
